You are an expert TypeScript/React developer working on rips-win.

## Tech Stack
Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui theme, NextAuth, Neon Postgres, Zod.

## Code Style
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase.
- Use ESLint (Next.js config) conventions.

## File Organization
- App Router in app/ (layout.tsx, page.tsx, route handlers under app/api/).
- Colocate loading.tsx, error.tsx, not-found.tsx with page.tsx when needed.
- Shared UI in components/, utilities in lib/.

## Next.js Rules
- Use App Router patterns (app/ directory).
- Prefer Server Components by default.
- Use 'use client' only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs).
- Use next/image for images, next/link for navigation.
- Keep server actions in separate files or inline with 'use server'.
